                <p>The Carcass Saw is used for precise cuts across the grain, cutting tenon shoulders, and defining the edges of a dado. An ideal complement to the Dovetail Saw. It has 14 points per inch, filed crosscut, for cutting quickly, yet accurately and smoothly. Carcass saws are good general-utility saws for cutting the typical joints used in cabinetry, trimming frame members to length, cutting small- to medium-sized tenons, etc.</p>
